The government says it can ramp up weekend COVID-19 vaccinations now that it has secured more funding. President Cyril Ramaphosa wants at least 300,000 vaccinations done daily. eNCA’s Heidi Giokos is at a private Discovery vaccination site in Johannesburg with the latest. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Authorities say they are doing all they can to make vaccinations convenient. Government says it can now ramp up weekend vaccinations after securing more funding. READ: COVID-19 | Increased infection will lead to more deaths - expert President Cyril Ramaphosa wants at least 300,000 jabs done daily. The private sector in Gauteng has been at the forefront, administering vaccinations over the weekend at some sites. Watch the video above for more details on this story